      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>remaining chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and the <strong>peeled garlic</strong> to a <strong>food processor </strong>with the <strong>lime zest</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>ginger paste </strong>and<strong> </strong>the juice of the <strong>remaining lime[s]</strong></p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>coconut</strong> <strong>marinade</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't have a food processor? Chop the ingredients and grind to a paste in a pestle & mortar instead!</p>",
